Compute the SemiDeviation() of the monthly returns.
http://www.rdocumentation.org/packages/PerformanceAnalytics/functions/DownsideDeviation

Use the function VaR() to estimate the 5% and 2.5% value-at-risk of a monthly investment in S&P 500 returns.
Use the function ES() to estimate the 5% and 2.5% expected shortfall of a monthly investment in S&P 500 returns.



# Calculate the SemiDeviation
SemiDeviation(sp500_monthly)

               sp500_monthly
Semi-Deviation    0.03334653






# Calculate the value at risk
VaR(sp500_monthly,
    p = 0.05)
    
    sp500_monthly
VaR   -0.07152617



VaR(sp500_monthly,
    p = 0.025)
    
    sp500_monthly
VaR   -0.09775359






# Calculate the expected shortfall
ES(sp500_monthly,
   p = 0.05)
   
   sp500_monthly
ES    -0.1180061



ES(sp500_monthly,
   p = 0.025)
   
   sp500_monthly
ES    -0.1653925




calculate the potential risk of your investments! Each statistic tells you something slightly different. It is important that you remember what your risk measures are!
